# PAYMENT DUE DATES

Current charges are considered past due after the due date. If the amount due for the current charges is not paid by the due date, the balance will be subject to a 1% late penalty with a $5.00 minimum. All customers are eligible to one waived late payment penalty per calendar year which will not appear on your bill.

# SIX EASY WAYS TO PAY

Online: Visit http://bit.ly/DiqIPay-Aquastar to enroll in our DigiPay/Aquastar portal. Payments are accepted seven days a week, 24 hours a day.

**Bank Draft:** Search "Utility Billing" at www.townofcarv.org to print out the enrollment form and return by mail to: Town of Cary, PO BOX 8049, Cary, NC 27512-8049; or, scan and send by email to utilityaccounts@townofcarv.org.

**Phone:** We accept Visa/MasterCard payments. Call (919) 469-4050 to speak with a Customer Service Representative Monday through Friday, 8 a.m.-5 p.m.

**Drop Boxes:** These brown boxes are located at Cary Town Hall and Bond Park Senior Center parking lots. Payments are collected Monday through Friday only.

**US Mail:** Please send your payments with the enclosed payment stub to our remittance address:

Town of Cary
PO BOX 71090
Charlotte, NC 28272-1090

**In Person:** We welcome your payment in person at the Finance Window inside of Cary Town Hall at 316 N. Academy Street during office hours, 8 a.m.-5 p.m.

*If service has been interrupted and payment has been made, please call our office to have your service reconnected.

# SERVICE DISCONNECTION-RECONNECTION

Most Cary utility customers satisfy their bills on time. In the event we do not receive payment within 10 days beyond the due date, your service becomes subject to disconnection. Reconnection will only be made upon the payment of the past due amount, including late and nonpay fees. If you are not able to satisfy your account by the date due, please contact us immediately at (919) 469-4050.

# RETURNED PAYMENTS

Customers will be charged the maximum state allowable returned payment fee.

# WRITTEN CORRESPONDENCES

To ensure prompt replies and faster delivery, please send correspondence to utilityaccounts@townofcarv.org or mail correspondences separate from your payments to the following address:

Town of Cary
ATTN: Utility Accounts
PO BOX 8049
Cary, NC 27512-8049

# MORE INFORMATION

Learn more about water, irrigation, sewer and other Town Services at www.townofcarv.org.

## DEFINITIONS

- TDU - CenterPoint Energy Transmission Distribution Surcharges
- Min Usage Fee - assessed when the energy consumption value is less than or equal to the specified contract kWh amount per billing period.
- kW - Kilowatt, the standard unit for measuring electricity demand, equal to 1,000 watts;
- kWh - Kilowatt-hour, the standard unit for measuring electricity energy consumption, equal to 1,000 watt-hours
- Assessments - Includes Gross Receipts Reimb. and PUC Assessments Reimbursement
- Avg. Price - Average price you paid for electric service this month (in cents per Kilowatt hour). Included in the calculation of Average Price is Energy Charges, TDU and PUC Assessment Reimb.
